<TITLE> Stocks fall 1 percent as Citigroup extends decline </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW YORK, Nov 5 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The Dow industrials and S&P 500 index fell 1 percent on Monday as shares of Citigroup extended their decline to session lows. The bank's warning of mounting loan losses also sparked a sell-off in shares of other financial companies. The Dow Jones industrial average was down 137.62 points, or 1.01 percent, at 13,457.48. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index was down 17.51 points, or 1.16 percent, at 1,492.14. The Nasdaq Composite Index was down 31.74 points, or 1.13 percent, at 2,778.64. 
